Open Project-management-application folder in IDE.

In order to connect to mysql server the application needs credentials.

Setting up IntelliJ when importing the project ---->
    1. Go to Project Structure
    2. Go to Project ---> set Project SDK to 11
    3. Set Project language level to 14 (Switch expressions)
    4. Go to Modules and select the java folder as Source folder (if it is not done automatically)
    5. Select test folder as Test


And then you may hit run and have fun : )

P.S. In order to run tests you must enter your credentials in init() methods in the test folder classes.
